1 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES - FLOOR VERSION
2 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
3 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
4 HOUSE BILL 4229 By: Kannady of the House
5 and
6 Murdock of the Senate
7
8
9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to public buildings and public works;
allowing school districts or public schools to
11 declare an emergency for purposes of entering an
emergency contract; providing conditions that must
12 exist; limiting the scope of emergency declarations
to contracts and actions to restore occupancy and
13 permit return of displaced students; clarifying what
emergency declarations shall not apply to; requiring
14 emergency declarations to be approved by governing
board; requiring emergency declarations to be
15 documented and retained as part of public record;
clarifying section does not limit other granted
16 emergency contracting authority; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
17
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 130.1 of Title 61, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
HB4229 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 A. Notwithstanding any other provision of the Oklahoma
2 Competitive Bidding Act, a school district or public school may
3 declare an emergency for purposes of entering into an emergency
4 contract pursuant to Section 130 of this title only when one or more
5 of the following conditions exist:
6 1. No Occupancy. A school building or facility is not occupied
7 by students, faculty, staff, or the public due to damage, unsafe
8 conditions, or the failure or loss of essential building systems; or
9 2. Student Displacement. Students who would normally attend
10 classes in the affected building or facility have been displaced,
11 reassigned, or relocated to alternative instructional settings due
12 to damage, unsafe conditions, or the failure or loss of essential
13 building systems.
14 B. An emergency declared pursuant to this section shall be
15 limited solely to contracts and actions necessary to restore
16 occupancy of the facility or permit the return of displaced
17 students, including emergency repair, remediation, replacement of
18 essential systems, or temporary instructional facilities.
19 C. An emergency declaration under this section shall not apply
20 to:
21 1. Routine maintenance;
22 2. Planned renovations or capital improvements;
23 3. Projects undertaken for convenience, cost savings, or
24 project acceleration; or
HB4229 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 4. Any condition in which the school facility remains occupied
2 and students are not displaced.
3 D. Any emergency declaration made pursuant to this section
4 shall:
5 1. Be approved by the governing board of the school district or
6 public school;
7 2. Be documented in writing, stating the specific facts
8 supporting the emergency declaration; and
9 3. Be retained as part of the public record in accordance with
10 the Oklahoma Open Records Act.
11 E. Nothing in this section shall be construed to expand or
12 limit the emergency contracting authority otherwise provided in
13 Section 130 of this title, but rather to define and limit the
14 circumstances under which a school district or public school may
15 invoke such authority.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
